# Known-good DEPLOYED binary baseline for `west darling-doctor` check 3.
#
# These are the md5s of the last-known-good deployed closure binaries in the install prefix. The
# doctor compares the deployed dyld (both copies) / mldr / darlingserver against these by default.
#
# Format: one "key = md5" per line; '#' comments. Keys: dyld, mldr, dserver.
# UPDATE this file (and note why + which Bead) whenever a legitimate rebuild changes what is
# deployed — otherwise the doctor will (correctly) flag the new deploy as a baseline mismatch.
#
# Current baseline (2026-07-04, task #116 A0-ARCH stage 2b): darlingserver updated to the
# A0-ARCH stage 2b landing: run-state AUTHORITY flipped to the MicroState machine --
# _running/_suspended are derived views updated only by the transition function; the
# impersonation lockout is its own _impersonationPin; doWork/suspend/inline paths read
# the state field (preDispatchParked / parkedContextIntact carry the dispatch-window
# facts). Includes the tape-caught repark fix (a no-op dispatch of a Parked thread must
# repark, not idle -- fuzz boot wedge otherwise). Branch fix/a0-arch-redesign, see
# tests/A0-ARCH-STAGE2.md. Acceptance: quick gate 15/15 gating green (synth + brew xz
# 2/2 strict), zero mstate violations; perf A/B in the baseline corridor (nestwait
# 3626/3674/3644, 300xtrue 2s); one non-reproducing nestwait-off teardown death (8/8
# green under gdb) = pre-existing #114-family watch item. dyld/mldr unchanged.
#   dyld    79b22273  (dyld-733.6, boot-compatible with the deployed 06-15 closure)
#   mldr    f0cd2a82  (perf#21b compact-fd band)
#   dserver 47ac175d  (ring + A0 a3de8c2 + A0-ARCH stages 0/1 + 2a/2b state machine)
# Previous dserver baselines: e50a3450 (2a), a889e85f (stage 1, .bak in darling-prefix/bin),
# 886d13af (a3de8c2, task #113).

dyld    = 79b22273481ea61ab63c0606c23ab300
mldr    = f0cd2a82efc4cb4614b63cabac0168f8
dserver = 47ac175da32f70d17bf05ff3c02eec28
